 meaning ‘bright-headed’, later understood as ‘frequenting churches’ (Irish <i>ceall</i>). There are several early Irish saints who bore this name. <i>Kelly</i> is now the most common of all surnames in Ireland.","Scottish: habitational name from either the lands of Kelly, near Arbroath (Angus), Kellie in Carnbee (Fife), or Kelly in Methlick (Aberdeenshire). Each of these placenames is from Pictish <i>celli</i> or Gaelic <i>coille</i> ‘wood’ + the placename forming suffix <i>-in</i>. Alternatively, from the lands of Kelloe in the barony of Hume (Berwickshire), whose name is of uncertain origin."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Benomom O'Kelly was born about 1380, in Inchiquin, County Galway, Ireland as the daughter of Murtogh Maeleachlann O'Kelly Chief. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Lord Ulick An Fhiona de Burke 3rd Of Clanricarde. She died in Ireland."},"et":{"about 1380–":"umbes 1380–Surnud","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1364–1424":"1364–1424","1396–1485":"1396–1485","1397–1480":"1397–1480","1350–1401":"1350–1401","1424":"1424","about 1380":"umbes 1380","1401":"1401","1397":"1397","1485":"1485","1364":"1364","1396":"1396","1350":"1350","1480":"1480","about 1397":"umbes 1397","1380":"1380","Connaught Bridge, County Kildare, Ireland":"Connaught Bridge, County Kildare, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Clanricarde, Galway, Connaught, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Iirimaa","Inchiquin, County Galway, Ireland":"Inchiquin, County Galway, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 1380–":"noin 1380–Kuollut","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1364–1424":"1364–1424","1396–1485":"1396–1485","1397–1480":"1397–1480","1350–1401":"1350–1401","1424":"1424","about 1380":"noin 1380","1401":"1401","1397":"1397","1485":"1485","1364":"1364","1396":"1396","1350":"1350","1480":"1480","about 1397":"noin 1397","1380":"1380","Connaught Bridge, County Kildare, Ireland":"Connaught Bridge, County Kildare, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti","Clanricarde, Galway, Connaught, Ireland":"Clanricarde, County Galway, Irlanti",